'''Moira Gemmill''' (18 September 1959 – 9 April 2015) was head of design and exhibitions at the [[Museum of London]] and director of design at the [[Victoria and Albert Museum]] from 2002 until early 2015. She had recently been appointed to the job of director of capital programmes at the [[Royal Collection Trust]]. Gemmill died after being in collision with a lorry at the Millbank roundabout, near [[Lambeth Bridge]], while cycling from her home at Kennington to her job at [[St James's Palace]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/11527969/Moira-Gemmill-design-director-obituary.html|title=Moira Gemmill, design director – obituary|date=10 April 2015|work=Telegraph.co.uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2015/apr/19/moira-gemmill|title=Moira Gemmill obituary|work=the Guardian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-london-32249804|title=Tributes paid to killed cyclist Moira Gemmill|work=BBC News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/cyclist-death-arts-and-design-visionary-moira-gemmill-killed-by-hgv-on-way-to-work-10168021.html|title=Cyclist death: Arts and design visionary Moira Gemmill killed by HGV on way to work|work=The Independent}}</ref>
On 20 April 2015, pressure group [[Stop Killing Cyclists]] held a "die-in" at the site of Gemmill's death to protest the number of cyclists dying on British roads.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.architectsjournal.co.uk/news/cyclists-hold-vigil-for-moira-gemmill/8681533.article|title=Cyclists hold vigil for Moira Gemmill|work=architectsjournal.co.uk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/london/hundreds-of-cyclists-hold-diein-vigil-at-lambeth-bridge-after-death-of-moira-gemmill-10191012.html|title=Cyclists hold 'die-in' vigil at Lambeth Bridge after death of Moira Gemmill|work=The Evening Standard}}</ref>
